{
  "name": "Bhai Surjit Singh (ex-Hazoori Raagi Amritsar)",
  "url": "https://kirtansewa.net/index.php/bhai-surjit-singh-ex-hazoori-raagi-amritsar/",
  "image_url": "https://cdn.kirtansewa.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/21230224/Bhai-Surjit-Singh-Amritsar-1-B.-Joginder-S.-and-B.-Kashmir-S..jpg",
  "body": [
    "At the moment, we only have very little information about Bhai Surjit Singh Ji. Bhai Sahib is originally from Sangrur, Punjab but is known as ‘Amritsar wale’ because of his service as a Hazoori Raagi in Sri Harmandir Sahib, Amritsar. Prior to forming his own jatha, he also accompanied Bhai Bakshish Singh Ji. Bhai Surjit Singh Ji moved to the United States sometime in the 1990s and performed Kirtan duties in Richmond Hill and Flushing before moving to New Jersey, where he currently resides. His ‘saathis’ include Bhai Joginder Singh Ji on the side harmonium and Bhai Kashmir Singh Ji on tabla. He was also accompanied on the side harmonium by Bhai Manjit Singh Ji, who is now based in California. If anyone has more information or recordings of Bhai Surjit Singh Ji, please contact us."
